  "text": "In order to get a super-resolved output from a single LR depth map, the method ATGV-Net [CITATION_1] 18 attempts to combine CNN with an energy minimization model, in the form of a powerful variational model. They improvise SRCNN to estimate, in addition to refining the depth map, the locations of discontinuities in the HR output depth maps. The refined depths and the located discontinuities serve as input to a variational model wherein pairwise regularization is carried out via anisotropic Total Generalized Variation (TGV) [CITATION_2] , with weights dependent on the network output. The output is the final HR estimate of the depth map. The authors train their model entirely on their own synthetic depth data. For benchmarking however, they use four different datasets; two derived from Middlebury and one each from Laserscan and ToFMark. The method is demonstrated to show better results in comparison to different state of the art methods, especially [CITATION_3] which is shown to be second best. Fig. 21 : Depth SR by [CITATION_4] .",
